A potentially fatal mistake.  After 51. Kxf2 Kf4, 52. Bxf3 ensures that Black is unable to Queen either pawn before White can Queen the c pawn.  Much better is 50. ... Kf4.  Then if 51. Bxf3, Kxf3 52. c6 g2#; or if 51. c6, e3 52. c7 g2# (52. Bxf3 Kfx3 53. c7 g2# lasts one more move).
